<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Border and Alignment Example</title>
    <style>
        /* General styles for body */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }

        /* Container with border */
        .container {
            border: 2px solid #4CAF50; /* Green border */
            padding: 20px; /* Padding inside the border */
            margin: 20px auto; /* Center the container */
            width: 80%; /* Width of the container */
            background-color: white; /* Background color */
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); /* Soft shadow */
        }

        /* Header style */
        h1 {
            text-align: center; /* Center align text */
            color: #333;
        }

        /* Paragraph style */
        p {
            text-align: justify; /* Justify paragraph text */
            color: #555;
            line-height: 1.5; /* Line height for readability */
        }

        /* Footer style */
        footer {
            text-align: center; /* Center align footer text */
            margin-top: 20px; /* Margin above footer */
            color: #777;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Container for the content -->
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Welcome to the Border and Alignment Example</h1>
        <p>
            This is a simple example to demonstrate how to use borders and alignment in HTML and CSS. 
            You can see how the text is aligned, and how the borders enhance the visual appearance 
            of the elements on the page. The container has padding inside the border to make it 
            look more aesthetically pleasing.
        </p>
        <p>
            CSS allows you to style your HTML elements easily, making your webpages look beautiful 
            and well-structured. You can experiment with different border styles, colors, and alignments 
            to create your desired layout.
        </p>
    </div>

    <footer>
        &copy; 2024 Border and Alignment Example
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
